<br>
<div align=left>
<b><font color=#76100A style='font-size: 12px'>&nbsp;&nbsp;Sorting</font></b>
<p style='padding-left: 10px'>
&#149;&nbsp;You can change the default sorting <b>order</b> if you click on one of the column heads.<br>
&#149;&nbsp;First click changes the sort key to the selected column, a second click on the same column reverses the order.<br>
</p>
<br>
<b><font color=#76100A style='font-size: 12px'>&nbsp;&nbsp;Filtering</font></b>
<p style='padding-left: 10px'>
&#149;&nbsp;The fields from the third header line allow quick filtering of the jobs.<br>
&#149;&nbsp;Type the text you want to search for in the field and press <i>Enter</i>.<br>
&#149;&nbsp;You can filter the <b>run number</b> by either a exact run (a single number) or as a range of run numbers (e.g. 1-100).<br>
</p>
<br>
<b><font color=#76100A style='font-size: 12px'>&nbsp;&nbsp;Other features</font></b>
<p style='padding-left: 10px'>
&#149;&nbsp;To see the original <b>JDL</b> file you can click on any PID from the second column.<br>
&#149;&nbsp;The <i>Type of job</i> and <i>Remarks</i> fields are truncated, you can see the full text going with the mouse over the text. Click on the text to get a persistent window with the full comment.<br>
</p>
</div>
